OL,3,CHottest January on record shatters
OL,4,Cglobal temperatures
OL,6,FOn land, the average temperature in
OL,7,FEurope was some 2.51C above the 1991-
OL,8,F2020 average for January, ITV News'
OL,9,FFaye Barker explains
OL,11,FLast month was the warmest January on
OL,12,Frecord, leaving scientists alarmed at
OL,13,Fthe speed of climate change.
OL,15,FJanuary 2025 was expected to be
OL,16,Fslightly cooler than the previous
OL,17,Fyear's - itself the hottest recorded
OL,18,FJanuary - because of the "La Nina"
OL,19,Fweather pattern in the Pacific that
OL,20,Fcools global temperatures.
