OL,4,Cglobal temperatures
OL,6,FThe C3S's analysis uses billions of
OL,7,Fmeasurements from satellites, ships,
OL,8,Faircraft and weather stations around
OL,9,Fthe world.
OL,11,FSamantha Burgess, Deputy Director of
OL,12,Fthe C3S, said: "January 2025 is
OL,13,Fanother surprising month, continuing
OL,14,Fthe record temperatures observed
OL,15,Fthroughout the last two years, despite
OL,16,Fthe development of La Nina conditions
OL,17,Fin the tropical Pacific and their
OL,18,Ftemporary cooling effect on global
OL,19,Ftemperatures."
