OL,3,CHottest January on record shatters
OL,4,Cglobal temperatures
OL,6,FDue to La Nina, temperatures were
OL,7,Fbelow average in the central Pacific.
OL,8,FBut, they were close to or above
OL,9,Faverage in the eastern Pacific ` which
OL,10,Fscientists say suggests a slowing or
OL,11,Fstalling of the move to La Nina
OL,12,Fconditions. Sea surface temperatures
OL,13,Fwere unusually high in many other
OL,14,Foceans and seas.
OL,16,FMrs Burgess said: "Copernicus will
OL,17,Fcontinue to closely monitor ocean
OL,18,Ftemperatures and their influence on
OL,19,Four evolving climate throughout 2025."
