OL,3,CHottest January on record shatters
OL,4,Cglobal temperatures
OL,6,FOn land, the average temperature in
OL,7,FEurope was 1.8C, some 2.51C above the
OL,8,F1991-2020 average for January. That
OL,9,Fmakes it the second warmest January
OL,10,Ffor the continent after 2020.
OL,12,FTemperatures were most above average
OL,13,Fover southern and eastern Europe, but
OL,14,Fbelow average in the UK and Ireland,
OL,15,FIceland, northern France and northern
OL,16,FScandinavia.
